title: 3D Printer Bed
description:
We stock a diverse range of replacement 3D printer bed plates, including original PCB options as well as upgraded cast aluminum and graphite build plates, tailored for Creality 3D printers and DIY Voron, ZeroG 3D printers. Ensure optimal adhesion, durability, and performance in your 3D printing projects with our high-quality bed plate solutions.
Comparison of Bed Plate Materials




Material
Benefits
Cons




PCB (Printed Circuit Board)
- Good for basic applications - Lightweight and cost-effective - Works well with many filaments
- Less durable compared to aluminum or graphite - Can warp over time with high temperatures


Cast Aluminum
- Excellent heat distribution - Durable and long-lasting - Provides good flatness
- Heavier than other options - Can be more expensive upfront, require heat soak


Graphite
- Highly resistant to warping - Good thermal conductivity, minimal heat soak
- Can be prone to scratches/dents - Needs careful handling to avoid damage



 
Choosing the right bed plate material depends on your specific needs and printing requirements. PCB plates are budget-friendly but less durable, while cast aluminum offers durability and excellent heat distribution at a higher cost. Graphite plates provide lightweight options with great heat conductivity, but may require more care during use. Evaluate the benefits and cons to find the best fit for your 3D printing endeavors!

title: ABS and ASA 1.75mm Filament
description:
ABS (Acrylonitrile Butadiene Styrene) and ASA (Acrylonitrile Styrene Acrylate) filament, known for their toughness and resistance to heat and UV (ASA), making them ideal for outdoor and functional prints. These filaments are perfect for projects that demand durability and reliability.
Key Features and Applications

ABS and ASA filaments are suitable for projects that require:

High impact resistance
Heat resistance
UV resistance (ASA)
Durability and reliability


Ideal applications include:

Outdoor functional prints
Industrial parts
Automotive components
Consumer products



Improving ABS Weatherability and UV Resistance
To enhance the weatherability and UV resistance of ABS prints, consider the following options:

Clear coat or paint/spray the printed part
Suitable for light UV exposure, such as under shade (ABS)
Note that ASA filament already offers improved UV resistance compared to ABS

Benefits and Considerations
When working with ABS and ASA filaments, consider the following benefits and factors:

Benefits:

High durability and reliability
Resistance to heat and UV (ASA)
Suitable for outdoor and functional prints


Considerations:

May require post-processing for improved weatherability and UV resistance (ABS)
ASA filament may be more suitable for applications with high UV exposure



We offer a variety of sparkle ASA/ABS as well as regular options from DREMC and Polymaker. Additionally, our range includes fiber-reinforced filaments, both glass and carbon, suitable for a wide range of applications, including DIY Voron printed parts and industrial projects. Experience exceptional performance and versatility with our high-quality filaments!
